holding.name: Remote enable
holding.description: Primary run/stop flag. Set to 1 to allow AC output; 0 places the inverter in standby.

holding.name: Grid safety function enables
holding.description: Bitfield enabling optional grid-code features such as ride-through curves, DRMS, and safety relays. Bits set to 1 activate the corresponding function.

holding.name: Firmware revisions
holding.description: Registers 9–14 store two ASCII revision blocks: 9–11 report the inverter firmware, while 12–14 hold the control/communication board firmware.

holding.name: Modbus baud rate
holding.description: Selects the RTU baud rate used by the RS485 interface.

holding.name: Serial number
holding.description: 10-character factory serial number (two ASCII characters per register).

holding.name: Model code
holding.description: Encodes inverter hardware options; decoding varies per product family.

holding.name: Firmware update trigger
holding.description: Writing the documented magic value starts the bootloader firmware update routine.

holding.name: Reset user configuration
holding.description: Clears user-tuned parameters (grid codes, limits) back to defaults when written with the documented key.

holding.name: Factory reset
holding.description: Restores factory configuration and clears history counters when executed with the vendor key.

holding.name: Manufacturer string
holding.description: Eight registers containing an ASCII manufacturer descriptor.

holding.name: Device type
holding.description: Growatt device type identifier mapped to human-friendly product names.

holding.name: Trackers / phases
holding.description: High byte = MPPT tracker count, low byte = AC phase count.

holding.name: Modbus Version
holding.description: Reported Modbus protocol revision (raw value divided by 100).

holding.name: Modbus Version
holding.description: Reported Modbus protocol revision (raw value divided by 100).

holding.name: Serial number
holding.description: 10-character factory serial number (two ASCII characters per register).
